We can get the checksum value (SHA256, SHA1, MD5) using the below curl command only if the packages are cached or locally deployed in Artifactory.

 
{code:java}
1. curl -uadmin:password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/generic-local/<filename>.sha256
fcdbaa6abbc8330b17c59454379dd3df0300f5a5edc4368baea868ca12cda8e6 

2. curl -uadmin:password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/generic-local/<filename>.md5
54eec02e942f50ffea7e147f33cd85f7 

3. curl -uadmin:password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/generic-local/<filename>.sha1
f2e52ef54166788ae29b5b4eec6fdb9cd580acab {code}
However, we cannot get the same checksum value of the packages from the source registry using the remote repository unless that package is cached. This breaks the working of a tool called "Kops". This tool "Kops" will first get the checksum value of a package from the source registry and then download it.

 

For example, when we create a generic remote repository pointing to "*https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/*" and try to get the checksum value of any file which is available in the source googleapis registry fails with 404.

 
{code:java}
curl -uadmin:Password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/googleapi/release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl.sha256
{
 "errors" : [ {
 "status" : 404,
 "message" : "Checksum not found for release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl"
 } ]
}{code}
Once the package "*kubectl*" is downloaded and it is cached in Artifactory, the above curl to get the checksum will be successful.
{code:java}
curl -uadmin:Password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/googleapi/release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl -o kubectl

curl -uadmin:Password http://localhost:8081/artifactory/googleapi/release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl.sha256
6ea8261b503c6c63d616878837dc70b758d4a3aeb9996ade8e83b51aedac9698{code}
This breaks the way the tool "Kops" works. Also, whenever there is already the checksum value available in the source registry, Artifactory should take it from there, if the package is not locally available.

 
{code:java}
For instance this binary: https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl
also has this checksum file published: https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v1.18.2/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl.sha256
{code}
So if the checksum file is already available for a specific package in the source registry as above, Artifactory should fetch it from the source if the package is not locally cached.

