Hello,


Due to security reasons, our servers doesn't have access to the Internet. Then, we use our Artifactory to download and keep in cache a lot of packages from external sources.


Some of our developpers came with a new need : remote repositories for Symfony 4, which is a problem beceause it uses 2 different kinds of repositories to download packages for installations and update :
 * php composer, as before
 * Symfony Flex which provides recipes and packages with a different way of doing it : https://flex.symfony.com/




After a few tests, it appears that Artifactory can't handle Symfony Flex packages. Without it, we can't install properly our Symfony 4, because when the installation tries to contact the flex server through Artifactory, it doesn't find the requested files.


Here is how to reproduce it :

In your Artifactory :
 * Create remote repo type php composer connected to Packagist (old Symfony Repo) : [https://packagist.org|https://packagist.org/]
 * Create remote type type php composer or generic (tried both and non worked) connected to flex server : [https://flex.symfony.com|https://flex.symfony.com/]


On your testing machine :
 * install php composer : [https://getcomposer.org/download/]
 * disable internet access from your test machine or you will not see the error to contact Symfony Flex
 * Configure composer remote repositories like this :
{{~/.composer/config.json}}
{{{}}
{{    "repositories": [}}
{{        \{"type": "composer", "url": "https://artifactory-principale.enedis.fr/artifactory/api/composer/<your packagist repo>"},}}
{{        \{"packagist": false}}}
{{    ]}}
{{}}}
 * If your repo is not public, do not forget to configure also your ~/.composer/auth.json with the informations provided by Artifactory
 * In specific folder for installing symfony do this command to install an empty symfony : {{composer create-project symfony/website-skeleton --no-install}}
 * It will download and install all files from packagist but should provide you an error related to symfony flex
 * Go in folder website-skeleton
 * Edit composer.json and add these lines at the end of the file :

{{"extra": {}}{{        }}

{{"symfony": {}}{{            }}

{{"allow-contrib": false,}}{{            }}

{{"require": "4.3.*",}}{{            }}

{{"endpoint": "Your repo connected to Flex URL"}}{{        }}

{{}}}{{    }}

{{}}}
 * Then do a composer update


You should have 404 errors because it couldn't find requested files to finish the update.

I found this project on Github to achieve this but it's still in developpement and we can't take that risk : https://github.com/sfeni/flexsrv


Can you add this feature to Artifactory ?

Thank you for your help.

Best regards,
Benedicte GARCIA

