At the moment, it's unclear from the docs how {{[baseRev]}} is used in sorting artifacts using the repo layout. As per my experimentation and questions asked to support, it looks like Semantic Version is partially implemented:
All is clear with the {{major.minor.bugfix}} part, as it follows SemVer

Pre-release, SemVer paragraph 9 (see below): 

{quote}9. A pre-release version MAY be denoted by appending a hyphen and a series of dot separated identifiers immediately following the patch version. Identifiers MUST comprise only ASCII alphanumerics and hyphen [0-9A-Za-z-]. Identifiers MUST NOT be empty. Numeric identifiers MUST NOT include leading zeroes. Pre-release versions have a lower precedence than the associated normal version. A pre-release version indicates that the version is unstable and might not satisfy the intended compatibility requirements as denoted by its associated normal version. Examples: {{1.0.0-alpha}}, {{1.0.0-alpha.1}}, {{1.0.0-0.3.7}}, {{1.0.0-x.7.z.92}}
{quote}

- We should use a hyphen for pre-release strings. This is fine, and complies with SemVer, but should be in the documentation
- Pre-release strings are sorted lexicographically as a whole. This is not compliant with SemVer, and poses the problem of sorting {{1.0.0-beta2}} and {{1.0.0-beta10}}


{{fileItegRev}} (or Build metadata in to SemVer jargon), SemVer paragraph 10:
{quote}10. Build metadata MAY be denoted by appending a plus sign and a series of dot separated identifiers immediately following the patch or pre-release version. Identifiers MUST comprise only ASCII alphanumerics and hyphen [0-9A-Za-z-]. Identifiers MUST NOT be empty. Build metadata SHOULD be ignored when determining version precedence. Thus two versions that differ only in the build metadata, have the same precedence. Examples: {{1.0.0-alpha+001}}, {{1.0.0+20130313144700}}, {{1.0.0-beta+exp.sha.5114f85}}.
{quote}

- Build metadata should be denoted by appending a '\+' sign. This can be done using the appropriate layout, but the Gradle/Ivy/Maved dependency declaration displayed in the GUI (and some REST API calls) will be wrong. Examples using this notation should be in the documentation, since SemVer is a widespread standard. This is my repo layout: {{[orgPath]/[module]/[baseRev]/[module]-[baseRev]+[fileItegRev].ext]}}
- SemVer specifications state that this data should be ignored when determining version precedence, which is fine. We still should be able to sort by build metadata in order to:
** Retrieve the latest build for a given version
** Use the build-in snapshot cleanup

I know this issues could be resolved via custom user plugins, but it's a bit of a waste to spend time developing something that it's already in Artifactory's functionality and should work out of the box.

I've focussed above comments on SemVer, but I think it's not the only standard out there: NuGet uses something a bit different, even it will fully support SemVer in version 3 and Python versioning is also different. For this reason, I think it would be awesome to have _version layouts_ for {{baseRev}} and {{fileItegRev}}. This layouts could provide a regex (already there in repo layouts) and a few rules to compare different versions

